task.summary: 2. When the timer starts for "kegel" we need a whistle sound, like a race starting. 3. When the timer starts for "rest" we need a horn sound, like a race ending 4. We need the tick sounds for the seconds on the kegel and rest screens. 5. We need to add a "Cancel" button at the bottom of the kegel/rest screen. I had told you only to put that button for infinite mode, but we need it for all modes 6. Currently, the cycles are counting down from 10/10 to 1/10, but we need it to start with 1/10 and go to 10/10, which is the standard in the US 8. Also, when you are on cycle one, it shows 10/10, and then when you move to cycle 2, it shows 10/10 again. When doing multiple cycles, it should add the cycles up and show the overall set number (10 sets from cycle 1, 10 sets from cycle 2 = 20 sets on the screen)
create pdf and than send it via gmail (work)
